column5: You guys are having a good week Mike.
Another beauty! They sure do pack on the feed bag this time of year
Incredible looking muskies! The first one is huge. They have a unique 'reticulated' appearance. Beauts!
What a beautiful fish!!!!   Good going!
gorgeous fish
We are lucky  Our musky usually have great colours to them
Very nice. must have been a great fight on light line !
Both beauty fish but that first one looks really special.
Beauty fish!
sweet!
What a beast

WOW, nice muskies Mike... Your da MUSKY man ! ! !  That area your fishing sure beats the bajesus out of trolling GB around in circles for 60+ hours hoping for one strike. Hope to get up to your waters next year so leave a few for me OK...

We were Lindy Riggin some big fall walleye the other day with minnows... Dad put his rod down to open another cold beverage... When he turned back around his rod was going over the side of the boat... With cat like reflexes he grabbed it just in time and wouldn't you know it there was his new PB musky on the end of the line...  No tape in the boat and didn't wanna do a vertical weigh on the boga grip so we will never know how big she "officially" was but it's probably the heaviest musky I've seen caught in person...    Mike
Fantastic fish Mike, congrats to your dad !!
Catchin' giant skis without even tryin"???  Wow! Very pretty looking specimen too.
Wow what a pig! Im loving the markings what a dark and beautiful fish!
wowsa.......just goes to show that you really don't need to do much to catch fish
Nice , love the leopard like spotting, very cool looking fish
Beautiful fish thanks for sharing
That's a supermodel of a musky.  Beauty.
I'd love to 'stumble' onto a musky like that as well.  Great job Mike!
awesome !!!! tankzilla........
What a fatty, Congrats....
Sharp looking ski!!

still waiting for my lottery number to ring up!  I still swear that I some time in my life i will run into a giant either tossing big baits for pike in the spring or jigging walleye in the fall.  Nice bloody fish!
so who said you need big baits to catch big Muskie???  Very nice fish, dad's straining under the weight..lol
Wow, that's awesome.  Congrats to your dad!
Beautiful fish! Breakout the Lindy rigs! Worms are also an option! LOL
nice fish there bud....
Wow, you don't need to stretch arm that fish to make it look big.  Nice catch and thanks for sharing.
Wow that's a beauty. I should take your dad out...I often stumble into some rather large walleye while musky fishing
Awesome!!!  Also shows youdont need 100lb braid to land a HYYUGE fish!
NICE ski!!!! No, you do not need 100lb braid to bring one in BUT you put the fish under a lot of stress to bring it in with lighter tackle. Much bigger chance of killing a trophy.
Of course!
Lucky dad.  Nice fish
Got another solid one today by accident...  I'll post the pic when I get it from my cousin...  And we got a 6-7 pound walleye with a 10" wide bite mark in it... Lmao!
